Edward J. Mathias

Edward J. Math­ias is a Man­ag­ing Direc­tor and Part­ner of The Car­lyle Group, a global pri­vate equity firm. Mr. Math­ias also serves as a member of the Board of Directors of The Carlyle Group as well as a mem­ber of the firm’s Growth Fund Invest­ment Com­mit­tees. Mr. Mathias was instru­men­tal in the found­ing of The Car­lyle Group and assisted in rais­ing the firm’s ini­tial cap­i­tal. Prior to join­ing Car­lyle in 1994, Mr. Math­ias was a mem­ber of the Man­age­ment Com­mit­tee and Board of Direc­tors of T. Rowe Price Asso­ciates, Inc., a major invest­ment man­age­ment orga­ni­za­tion. Mr. Mathias is a member of the USAID Private Capital Group for Africa (PCGA) Partners Forum, the President’s Advisory Council for Doing Business in Africa, and the Boards of Directors of Brown Advisory and Ambulnz. Mr. Mathias is a member of the Advisory Boards of Alberleen Group, Avondale Partners, LCatterton, Gold Bullion International, Skybridge Capital, Strategas, Trident Capital, and Ultra Capital.Mr. Math­ias holds an M.B.A. from the Har­vard Busi­ness School and an under­grad­u­ate degree from the Uni­ver­sity of Penn­syl­va­nia, where he presently serves as Trustee Emeritus of the Invest­ment Committee


